Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
read_stream(25.10)                                          read_stream(25.10)

Name
       read_stream  -  Reads in-stream files or a layer map and outputs a sum-
       mary of the cell names read in, and any layer/data types that have data
       with no map_file entry

Syntax
       read_stream

       [-help]

       -layer_map <layer_map_files>

       {[-pvs_fill ] | [[<in_files>] [-cells <cell_list> [-offset {x y}]]]}

       Reads in-stream files or a layer map and outputs a summary of the  cell
       names read in, and any layer/data types that have data with no map_file
       entry.  The  data is automatically scaled during reading to the correct
       DB units based on the stream units.

              * It reads in the metal fill stream data (with top cell name and
                offset) to overlay on the design. The fill data  is  displayed
                to  database fill shapes (equivalent to reading DEF FILL data)
                to allow editing or changing the fill data.

                Reading in fill data is done once per session.

              * It reads in-stream cells that have the same names  as  Innovus
                cell names to display the stream cell data (for example, over-
                lay  or  toggle  between  stream shapes and LEF shapes for the
                cells).

                If a stream cell name is repeated, it  replaces  any  previous
                data for that cell.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each read_stream parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man read_stream.

       -cells <cell_list>
              Reads only the specified cells from GDS files.

       <in_files>
              Lists GDS and OASIS files.

       -layer_map <layer_map_files>
              Specifies the layer map file to map GDS layer to design layer

       -offset <x><y>
              Specifies, in microns, the offset for the top-level fill cell.

       -pvs_fill
              Specifies to process the PVS FILL data in the read process.

       Layer Map File Format

       The -layer_map file maps stream layer/dtype data to Innovus  layer  and
       objects.  Stream data does not have net ids, so you can only map stream
       data for display, or to fill, fill_opc or fill_blockage shapes.

       The format for the layer map file is one line for each stream layer and
       dtype:

       <layer data_type layer_name object_type>

       Where

              * layer is an stream layer number. It is an integer.

              * data_type is a stream data_type number. It must be  either  an
                integer, or a range (e.g. 0-255).

              * layer_name  is normally must be a LEF (or OA tech) layer name.
                It can only be a "custom" layer name if the obj_type is  "dis-
                play"  (e.g. this data is not on any of the LEF layers, but is
                useful for display purposes). Any custom layer  data  will  be
                displayed    like   data   created   with   add_gui_shape   or
                add_gui_text. The layer_name is case-sensitive.

              * object_type is one of these keywords:

                * fill: Equivalent to DEF FILL shapes

                * fill_opc: Equivalent to DEF FILL with + OPC shapes

                * fill_blockage: Equivalent to DEF BLOCKAGE + FILLS shapes

                * display: Is only for display purposes, and cannot  be  flat-
                  tened.
              fill, fill_opc, and display can optionally be followed by

              :mask:<mask_num>

              where mask_num is the mask number for the shape for a multi-mask
              layer (equivalent of DEF + MASK <mask_num> for a shape).

              fill_blockage can optionally be followed by

              :name:<blockage_name>

              where<  blockage_name>  is  the  name given to all the blockages
              from this layer/dtype.

              Any text on the same layer/data_type will be mapped to the  same
              DB layer as a text object on that layer. About the TEXT font and
              size,  font  0  could  be default (or other font decided by RD).
              Size could use the original size in GDS and scale it if dbu mis-
              match to Innovus.

              The object_type keywords are case insensitive. The tool  ignores
              blank lines or lines beginning with #.

              A given layer/dtype combination can only appear once.

       Example of Stream map-file for metal fill, via-fill, and fill blockages

       #Stream map-file for metal fill, via-fill, and fill blockages

       #only metal1 has two masks

       #layer    dtype     layer_name     obj_type

       1         1         metal1         fill:mask:1

       1         2         metal1         fill:mask:2

       51        1         cut1           fill

       2         1         metal2         fill

       52        1         cut2           fill

       3         1         metal3         fill

       ...

       101       1         metal1         fill_blockage:name:blkg1

       101       2         metal1         fill_blockage:name:blkg2

       101       3-255     metal1         fill_blockage

       Example  of Stream map-file for cell-data to display on top of LEF cell
       data

       #Stream map-file for cell-data to display on top of LEF cell data

       #Only routing layers and the cell-outline on custom layer "outline"

       #are mapped. It does not show cut layers or layers below metal1.

       #layer    dtype     layer_name     obj_type

       1         0-255     metal1         display

       2         0-255     metal2         display

       #custom layer "outline" is created if it does not already exist

       100       1         outline        display

Examples
       Parse stream cells with specified layer map display stream cell data on
       top  of  LEF  cell  data.  The   report   output   is   redirected   to
       read_stream.rpt.

       >read_stream   {stdcells.gds  memory.gds}  -layer_map  gds_layer.map  >
       read_stream.rpt

       Read in metal-fill data and overlay it on the design. The  report  will
       be in the log file.

       >read_stream fill.gds -cell top_fill -layer_map gds_layer.map

       Example of output report

       #Cell names read in:

       top_fill

       fill_1

       fill_2

       ...

       #Layer/dtype data in the stream file with no map-file entry

       1    10

       4    1, 9

       ...

